cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.GR 

The paper deals with generative models and their attention mechanisms, which are commonly used in computer vision tasks. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel information theoretic criterion for designing sparse attention patterns, which falls under the category of machine learning and artificial intelligence, hence cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are also likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the inversion of Generative Adversarial Networks, which involves optimization techniques and neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a possible sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with two-dimensional geometry and locality, which falls under the category of graphics and visualization, making cs.GR (Graphics) a possible sub-category.
